SUMMARY:Cane Creek Mountains Natural Area
DESCRIPTION:Triangle Hiking and Outdoors Group\nWe will meet at the **Pine
  Hill Trailhead** in the Cane Creek Mountains Area\n\nhttps://parks.alaman
 cecountync.gov/outdoors-2/cane-creek-mountains-natural-area/\n\nand hike s
 everal of the trails for a total of 8.5 miles. It is nice and hilly but th
 e trails are well maintained and in good shape. Our pace will be about 3 m
 iles per hour. Dress for the weather\, bring water and snacks and\, since 
 there are lots of rocks and roots\, wear appropriate shoes.\nThere is a pi
 t toilet at the trailhead.\n\nBy participating in this event\, you agree t
 o the terms below:\n\nTRIP PARTICIPANT WAIVER OF LIABILITY I fully realize
  that this activity involves a risk of personal injury\, property damage\,
  or loss of my person or property. I hereby for myself\, my heirs\, execut
 ors and administrators\, and same for persons with whom are in my party\, 
 waive and release any claims or rights against Triangle Hiking & Outdoors 
 Group (THOG)\, all of its owners and coordinators for any and all injury\,
  damages or loss to my person or property incurred during this activity. I
  also understand that THOG organizers are not required\, nor should it be 
 assumed that they are CPR/First Aid/Wilderness Survival Certified and I am
  responsible for my own personal safety.
