SUMMARY:after work bike ride on the ATT 
DESCRIPTION:Triangle Hiking and Outdoors Group\nWe'll be starting near Sou
 thpoint and final starting point will be sent out Monday evening.\n\nMake 
 sure that your bike is in good working order - tires hold air and are up t
 o pressure\, brakes and shifters work and your chain has been oiled.\n\nWe
 'll be riding just over 1 1/3 hour and about 16 miles. The ride is fairly 
 flat and shaded and our pace will be moderate (about 12 mph average). I re
 commend a hard tail or hybrid bike\, but if you really want to bring a roa
 d bike it's ok\, though you'll likely be a bit bored. Unicycles....?\n\nI'
 ll be eating after the ride at a restaurant. You're welcome to join me if 
 you like.\n\nHelmets are required and by signing up you agree to THOG liab
 ility waiver statement.\n\nPlease Note!! Any cancellation less than 30 hou
 rs before the beginning of the event will be considered a "no show"
